problem.markdown:
>>How are grayscale images fed as input to a CNN?<<

(x) They are fed as a matrix of pixel values. {{Correct}}
( ) They are fed as convolutions. {{Convolutions are a mathematical operation that is the cornerstone of the CNN architecture.}}
( ) They are fed as a set of parameters. {{The parameters represent the model, not the images.}}
( ) They are fed as modular building blocks. {{The modular building blocks are used to construct CNN architectures, they are not the images as input.}}

||They range from 0 to 255.||
